The best way to do this would be with CSS. And when it comes to CSS with JavaFX it helps to read the [JavaFX CSS Reference Guide][1] which tells you the styleclasses and substructures of various JavaFX nodes.

In this case, you can do:

    .spinner .increment-arrow-button .increment-arrow {
        -fx-background-color: red;
    }

    .spinner .decrement-arrow-button .decrement-arrow {
        -fx-background-color: red;
    }

Then add the stylesheet to the `Scene` that the `Spinner` belongs to. This will change the arrows (which are `Region`s) to have a background with the color red.

[1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/9/docs/api/javafx/scene/doc-files/cssref.html#spinner

